    <item>
      <title>Architecture</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-service-mesh/about/architecture/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-service-mesh/about/architecture/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;F5 NGINX Service Mesh is an infrastructure layer designed to decouple application business logic from deep networking concerns. A mesh is designed to provide fast, reliable, and low-latency network connections for modern application architectures.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;architecture-and-components&#34;&gt;Architecture and Components  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#architecture-and-components&#34; title=&#34;Architecture and Components&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;NGINX Service Mesh deploys two primary layers: a &lt;strong&gt;control plane layer&lt;/strong&gt; that&amp;rsquo;s responsible for configuration and management, and a &lt;strong&gt;data plane layer&lt;/strong&gt; that provides the network functions valuable to distributed applications.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
